Text.Text: I'm Morohem, so-called Master of Chambers.  And you're...?
Well met, <CHARNAME>.  Not to be rude, but I know you haven't been sent to face the Eight Chambers, so...?

When an initiate masters all eight chambers and becomes a true monk, he or she becomes the current Master of the Chambers until the next challenger succeeds.  I'm the latest in a long line, so I sit down here waiting for the next one...
...my task is to open the way from chamber to chamber as well as offer instructions and advice should an initiate need it.  Being ominous and cryptic about it is entirely optional.

But I do... very much so.  What goes on in those eight rooms is beyond words - it's melodramatic enough that there's no need for me play at being some "wise but sinister Master of Chambers."  I'm simply here to help challengers.

I was once told they were designed to "thwart those without the skill or willpower to be worthy of our order" - and with Lathander as my witness, they *do.*  I don't know what madman concocted or created them, but mad he certainly was.
Not without permission, no.  The doors are sealed by spellcraft and only open by the Master of Chamber's will.
Well again, <CHARNAME>.
Ah, it's <CHARNAME>.  The chambers are open to you now.  Be careful: each chamber's test consists of a unique battle, and all are *deadly* - more than a few challengers have died within...
Well again, <CHARNAME> - the chambers are open to you.  Let me know when you're ready to face them.
The Chamber of Stone - pull the levers in the correct order and survive the resulting consequences to master the chamber.  If they're pulled in the wrong order, you must begin again.
The Chamber of Shadows - you must navigate a series of dark portals to master the chamber; the shadows can both help and hinder your progress.
The Chamber of Sorcery - there are a number of glowing panels in the floor... use them wisely to defeat the enemies within.
The Chamber of Clockwork - you will face a trio of foes within a room of whirling blades and drills.  Step carefully and defeat your opponents to master the chamber...
...but be wary of your enemies' final attacks.  The chamber itself will provide you with a method of stopping them.
The Chamber of Sand - the sand itself will attack you - find a way to defeat it to master the chamber.
The Chamber of Silk - poisonweb spiders have strung their venomous webs across the room and lurk in the dark corners, awaiting prey.  Defeat them all to master the chamber.
The Chamber of Battle - you must learn to manipulate your enemies in battle in order to master this chamber.
The Chamber of Immolation.  You must face your enemy in a hostile environment - huge gouts of flame constantly erupt from the floor.  Defeat them all to master the chamber.

When you are ready to face the chambers, let me know - I'll let you in and seal the door behind you, at which point the test will begin.  You may not leave until you have mastered the chamber... or perish in the attempt.

Congratulations, <CHARNAME>...  though I almost wish that you'd actually been joining the order so that you'd take my place down here for a time.  Ah, well.  Be sure to let Salisam know that you've succeeded!

Congratulations, <CHARNAME>...  though I almost wish that you'd actually been joining the order so that you'd take my place down here for a time.  Ah, well.  Be sure to let Aruma know that you've succeeded!
Lastly, so long as you're facing the chambers you're permitted to rest here.  Simply ask and I'll see to it that you're not disturbed.
For how long?
You must face each chamber alone and unarmed.  This means you may bring no companions and no equipment.  If you have items that require storage, speak to Nonin upstairs...
...by the way, should one of your companions choose to enter a chamber in your place, please have them speak to me...

...also, there is a hidden compartment in each of the chambers; the release switch is a large golden button.  Depress it and a small sliding door will reveal a number of weapons, should you require them...

No, you're not... you must face each chamber alone and unarmed; you may carry no equipment of any sort.  If you have items that require storage, speak to Nonin upstairs.  Please return when you're ready... farewell.
I... but... oh, very well.  I'll place your equipment over there, behind you, between the two flights of stairs.  Just don't forget where it is and leave everything behind.  And don't tell Nonin!
Certainly... here you are.
I'm <CHARNAME>.
